METADATAEXTENSION.NAME: SQL_Query
METADATAEXTENSION.VALUE: INSERT INTO VRAP.TICD_CMN_NM_ASSC (ICD_CD_GID,ICD_CMN_NM_GID,CRTE_USR_ID,CRTE_TS,UPDT_USR_ID,UPDT_TS) SELECT IC.ICD_CD_GID, ICN.ICD_CMN_NM_GID,?USR_ID?,CURRENT TIMESTAMP,?USR_ID?, CURRENT TIMESTAMP FROM VRAP.TICD_CD IC, VRAP.TICD_CMN_NM ICN WHERE ICD_CD = ?ICD_CD? AND ICN.ICD_CMN_NM_GID < 0;

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION:
This lookup will determine whether or not an ICD Common Name exists for the distinct list of ICD_CDs being extracted for the daily claims.
If a common name exists for the ICD_CD, then there will be multiple rows for that ICD_CD, one per CORP_CD. If a row is returned, then the assumption is that there is one row per corp in the table, and a common name does not have to be built.
If no row is returned then a row needs to be built for each corp.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: LKP_VICD_CD_CMN_NM

TRANSFORMFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This is the ICD_CD from the VRAP.TICD_CD table. The value originates from the EDM CAS data.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: ICD_CD

TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: ICD_CD_sq

TRANSFORMATION.NAME: AGG_Distinct_ICD_CD
